# Backend Specification

## Architecture

Go 1.24 server using chi/v5 router. Follows a strict **handler => service => repository** pattern with constructor-based dependency injection. No ORM — all database access is raw SQL via `lib/pq`.

## Package Layout

```
backend/
├── main.go                    # Entry: router setup, middleware wiring, server start
├── database/db.go             # PostgreSQL + Redis client initialization
├── models/
│   ├── models.go              # Shared data types (User, Thread, Product, Order, etc.)
│   └── site_config.go         # SiteConfig types (branding, SEO, footer, features)
└── internal/
    ├── auth/                  # JWT (HS256), bcrypt passwords, context helpers
    ├── middleware/             # CORS, JWT auth, optional auth, RBAC, rate limit, armed guard
    ├── user/                  # User CRUD, roles, permissions, suspension, Redis cache
    ├── forum/                 # Categories, threads, comments, likes, Redis cache
    ├── store/                 # Products, cart, orders, subscriptions, Stripe, Redis cache
    ├── cart/                  # Shopping cart API (add, remove, list, clear)
    ├── inbox/                 # 1-to-1 conversations + messages
    ├── notification/          # Per-user notifications (typed, routed, real-time)
    ├── config/                # site_config CRUD (branding, SEO, footer, features)
    ├── page/                  # CMS pages (slug-based, JSONB block content)
    ├── customsection/         # User-defined custom sections for pages
    ├── datasource/            # Data source definitions, compiler, TS runner
    ├── events/                # Event dispatcher and activity logging
    ├── upload/                # Image/video/file/banner uploads (user-isolated dirs)
    ├── ws/                    # WebSocket hub, presence, chat ring, cursor broadcast
    ├── ssr/                   # index.html rewriting with SEO head tags
    ├── utils/                 # Shared HTTP helpers
    ├── grengo/                # Admin dashboard API proxy
    ├── migrations/            # SQL schema (001), seed data (002), CMS schema (003)
    ├── integration/           # Integration test suite
    └── testutil/              # Test helpers (DB setup)
```

## Handler => Service => Repository Pattern

### Handlers (`handler.go`)

- Receive `http.Request`, decode JSON body, validate required fields
- Extract auth context via `auth.UserFromContext(r.Context())`
- Call service methods, write JSON response or error
- Never contain business logic or SQL

### Services (`service.go`)

- Contain all business logic
- Orchestrate repository calls
- Manage Redis cache (read-through with 5-min TTL, invalidate on writes)
- Dispatch WebSocket events via hub
- Return domain errors, not HTTP errors

### Repositories (`repository.go`)

- Execute raw SQL against PostgreSQL
- Accept `context.Context` as first parameter
- Return models or `error`
- No caching, no business logic

### Interfaces (`interface.go`)

- Define service and repository contracts per domain
- Enable test mocking

## Middleware Stack

All routes use composable chi middleware:

| Middleware     | Behavior                                                               |
| -------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| CORS           | Origin allowlist from `DOMAINS` env — no wildcards                     |
| JWT Auth       | Validates `Authorization: Bearer <token>`, injects claims into context |
| Optional JWT   | Enriches context when token present, doesn't block anonymous           |
| Permission     | Checks specific permission or admin role                               |
| Rate Limit     | 100 req/min general, 10 req/min auth (per IP via `httprate`)           |
| Armed Guard    | Blocks API traffic when tenant is in maintenance mode                  |
| Request Logger | Logs method, host, path, status, bytes, duration; redacts tokens       |
| X-Backend      | Identifies which tenant handled the request                            |
| Cache-Control  | `no-store` on all API responses                                        |

## Authentication & Authorization

- JWT access tokens: HS256, configurable TTL via `SESSION_TIMEOUT_MIN` (default 30)
- Refresh tokens: 7-day lifetime, stored in `user_sessions`
- Passwords: bcrypt cost 12, enforced 8–72 character length
- 4 default roles: admin, member, moderator, banned
- 18 granular permissions across forum, store, user management, presence, CMS
- Permissions resolve from role assignments + direct per-user grants
- Admin role implicitly holds all permissions
- Role/permission changes push new JWTs to affected users via WebSocket

## Database

PostgreSQL 16 with per-tenant databases on a shared instance.

### Connection Pool

- `DB_MAX_OPEN_CONNS`: 100
- `DB_MAX_IDLE_CONNS`: 50
- `DB_CONN_MAX_LIFETIME_MIN`: 30

### Migration Strategy

Idempotent SQL files in `internal/migrations/`:

- `001_schema.sql` — all tables with `IF NOT EXISTS`
- `002_seed.sql` — default roles, permissions, admin user
- `003_pages.sql` — CMS page schema

Prices stored as `BIGINT` cents. Timestamps are `TIMESTAMPTZ` with `DEFAULT NOW()`.

### Key Tables

- `users`, `user_sessions`, `roles`, `permissions`, `role_permissions`, `user_roles`, `user_permissions`
- `forum_categories`, `forum_threads`, `thread_comments`, `thread_likes`, `thread_comment_likes`
- `products`, `store_categories`, `cart_items`, `orders`, `order_items`, `payments`, `subscription_plans`, `subscriptions`
- `inbox_conversations`, `inbox_messages`, `notifications`
- `site_config`, `landing_sections`, `landing_items`, `pages`

## Cache Layer

Redis 7, namespaced per tenant (e.g. `home:user:42`, `writer:forum:thread:7`).

- Read-through cache with 5-minute TTL
- Automatic invalidation on writes
- Used for: users, threads, products, site config
- All cache operations are best-effort — cache misses fall through to DB

## WebSocket Hub

Single event loop dispatching to a bounded worker pool (default 256 goroutines).

| Feature                | Detail                                                       |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Resource subscriptions | Key-based pub/sub (e.g. `thread:42`) with targeted updates   |
| Presence               | Debounced broadcasts of online users + current routes        |
| Global chat            | Ring buffer (80 messages) with history replay on connect     |
| Cursor sharing         | Real-time mouse position relay to same-route users           |
| Teleport               | Admin can navigate any connected user to a route             |
| Permission push        | Role/permission changes push new JWT to affected connections |
| Targeted delivery      | `SendToUser(userID, msg)` reaches all concurrent connections |

Configurable: `WS_MAX_CONNECTIONS` (100K), `WS_MAX_WORKERS` (256), `WS_CHAT_RING_SIZE` (80), `WS_PRESENCE_INTERVAL_MS` (1000).

## Payments

Pluggable provider interface:

- `DemoPaymentProvider` — simulates transactions locally (configurable failure rate)
- `StripePaymentProvider` — PaymentIntents, Checkout Sessions, Customers, Subscriptions (Stripe API v82)

Set via `PAYMENT_PROVIDER` env (`demo` or `stripe`).

## File Uploads

- Per-user isolated directories: `uploads/users/{userID}/{type}/`
- Image: JPEG, PNG, WebP, GIF ≤ 10 MB with dimension validation
- Video: MP4, WebM, OGG, MOV ≤ 50 MB
- Directory-traversal protection (`..` rejection)
- nginx serves uploads with 30-day cache TTL

## SSR / SEO

`internal/ssr/` rewrites `index.html` at serve time, injecting:

- `<title>`, `<meta name="description">`, OG tags, favicon
- Values sourced from `site_config` table
- Dynamic sitemap at `/sitemap.xml`

## Testing

### Unit Tests

- Go test files alongside source (`*_test.go`)
- Repository tests use `testutil/db.go` for isolated DB setup
- Service tests mock repository interfaces

### Integration Tests

- `internal/integration/` — full HTTP test suite
- Covers: user registration/auth, forum CRUD, store checkout, uploads
- Uses real DB + Redis instances

### Frontend Tests

- Vitest + Testing Library
- Run via `npm test` in `backend/frontend/`

## API Routes

All under `/api/`. JWT-protected unless noted.

- `GET /health` — health check (no auth)
- `GET /time` — server UTC time (no auth)
- `GET /ws` — WebSocket (token via query param)
- `/auth/*` — register, login, refresh, logout
- `/users/*` — CRUD, roles, permissions, suspension
- `/forum/*` — categories, threads, comments, likes
- `/store/*` — products, cart, checkout, orders, subscriptions
- `/inbox/*` — conversations, messages, unread count
- `/notifications/*` — list, read, delete
- `/config/*` — branding, SEO, footer, features, landing, pages
- `/upload/*` — image, video, file, banner

### Page / Landing Endpoints

All under `/config/pages` (chi subroute).

| Method | Path                   | Auth      | Purpose                            |
| ------ | ---------------------- | --------- | ---------------------------------- |
| GET    | /landing-slug          | none      | Resolve configured landing slug    |
| GET    | /index                 | opt JWT   | Fetch landing page inline (legacy) |
| GET    | /list                  | none      | List all pages                     |
| GET    | /browse                | opt JWT   | Public feed with ownership data    |
| GET    | /{slug}                | opt JWT   | Fetch page by slug                 |
| GET    | /{slug}/comments       | opt JWT   | List page comments                 |
| POST   | /{slug}/view           | none      | Record page view                   |
| POST   | /                      | JWT+perm  | Create page                        |
| PUT    | /{id}                  | JWT+perm  | Update page content                |
| DELETE | /{id}                  | JWT+perm  | Delete page                        |
| POST   | /{id}/duplicate        | JWT+perm  | Duplicate page                     |
| PUT    | /landing-page          | JWT+perm  | Set landing page slug              |
| POST   | /factory-reset         | JWT+perm  | Delete all pages + reset config    |
| PUT    | /{id}/owner            | JWT+perm  | Set page owner                     |
| DELETE | /{id}/owner            | JWT+perm  | Clear page owner                   |
| POST   | /{id}/editors          | JWT+perm  | Add editor                         |
| DELETE | /{id}/editors/{userId} | JWT+perm  | Remove editor                      |
| POST   | /{id}/like             | JWT       | Like page                          |
| DELETE | /{id}/like             | JWT       | Unlike page                        |
| POST   | /{id}/comments         | JWT+limit | Create comment                     |
| PUT    | /comments/{commentId}  | JWT+limit | Update comment                     |
| DELETE | /comments/{commentId}  | JWT+limit | Delete comment                     |

**Critical: Landing page is config-driven.** The `landing_page_slug` key in
`site_config` determines which page renders at `/`. There is no `is_index`
column. See `route_resolution_spec` for the full data flow.

## Security Checklist

- bcrypt cost 12 for passwords
- HS256 JWT with env-sourced secret
- CORS explicit origin allowlist (no wildcards)
- Rate limiting per IP
- RBAC on all protected endpoints
- MIME type allowlist for uploads
- Path traversal guards on file serving
- Token redaction in logs
- `Cache-Control: no-store` on API responses
- Non-root container user (`appuser`)
- Configurable DB connection pool limits
